Worker. Diagnosis. This species is uniquely characterized by the following combination of features: (1) longitudinal rugae on cephalic dorsum rarely continue to posterior margin, (2) interrugae on cephalic dorsum and dorsum of promesonotum mostly smooth and shining, (3) posterior surface of petiolar node smooth and shining, (4) inferior propodeal spines triangular, height and width similar, notably shorter than superior spines, and (5) body mostly concolorous dark brownish-black to black (
Figure 6
).
